(Photo: Matthew Emmons, USA TODAY Sports) 1 CONNECT COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
What a comeback. Fox's Super Bowl LI averaged 111.3 million viewers Sunday, the lowest total since 2013 but still among the top 5 contests. The premiere of 24: Legacy , which followed at 11 ET, claimed just 17.6 million, the weakest post-Bowl turnout since ABC's Alias in 2003. 
The winner is.... President Trump's prime-time unveiling of his nominee for the Supreme Court, Neil Gorsuch, drew 33 million viewers Tuesday on eight networks. 
Jermaine Fowler and Judd Hirsch in CBS's 'Superior Donuts.' (Photo: Michael Yarish, CBS) 
More openers: A special preview of CBS' Superior Donuts (10.5 million same-day viewers) behind The Big Bang Theory (14.7 million) easily bested the opener of NBC's Powerless (3.1 million, both Thursday). But CBS drama Training Day dropped to 4.7 million. And CW's The 100 returned Wednesday with 1.2 million. <!--iframe--> Read or Share this story: http://usat.ly/2kKkz63 NEVER MISS OUT Life Be a pop culture maven.
